<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36210f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36210f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36210f"> 210(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> walking staff</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Like that choleric warrior Achilles, he <font color="green">[Stuyvesant]</font> was somewhat subject to extempore bursts of passion, which were rather unpleasant to his favorites and attendants, whose perceptions he was apt to quicken, after the manner of his illustrious imitator, Peter the Great, by anointing their shoulders with his <mark>walking-staff</mark>. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 206</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
